{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_57","type":"agent_message","text":"I’ve got the rollback boundary model sorted now: it can’t just truncate history at the latest rollback, because resumed work after a rollback must become visible again. I’m implementing the journal “prune old branch, keep new branch” logic alongside the rollback command so resume/history stay consistent after multiple rollbacks."}}
