{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_145","type":"agent_message","text":"# Implementation Notes\n\n## Decisions Made\n- Implemented durable rollback checkpoints in the run model, filesystem adapter, and engine; each successful stage transition now persists a `RollbackPoint` plus a `rollback_created` journal event.\n- Added logical rollback execution in the project-run service and CLI, including status/stage validation, snapshot restoration, monotonic `rollback_point_meta` updates, and `rollback_performed` journal events.\n- Applied rollback-aware journal replay to `run history`, `run tail`, and resume derivation so rolled-back branches are hidden while new post-rollback work remains visible.\n- Implemented hard rollback repository reset support through the worktree adapter, with logical rollback committed before any `git reset --hard` attempt.\n- Hardened NDJSON append behavior in the filesystem adapter so appending to journal files remains valid even when the existing file lacks a trailing newline.\n\n## Spec Deviations\n- None.\n\n## Testing\n- Added rollback-focused unit, adapter-contract, workflow-engine, CLI, and conformance-feature coverage.\n- Verified with `nix develop -c cargo test`.\n\n---"}}
